> Crispy chicken with melty cheddar and bold spices is a recipe for success. Once baked, the crust turns golden brown while the meat stays juicy and tender, served alongside tender roasted broccoli and cheesy, bacon-and-chive-studded mashed potatoes. Together, it's a meal as elegant as it is satisfying and delicious.

Cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Dice @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Finely chop @chives{¼%ounce}.

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Lightly oil a #baking sheet{}. Wash and dry produce.

Place @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4) in a medium #microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave until melted, ~{30%seconds}. Stir in @panko breadcrumbs{¼%cup}, half the @fry seasoning{1/2%tbsp}, half the @cheddar cheese{¼%cup} (you'll use the rest of the seasoning and cheese later), @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season with remaining @fry seasoning{1/2%tbsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Place on one side of prepared #sheet{} (for 4 servings, spread out across entire sheet).

Evenly spread a thin layer of @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} onto tops of chicken (you might not use all the mayo); mound with panko mixture, pressing to adhere (no need to coat the undersides).

Toss broccoli on opposite side of sheet from chicken with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper. (For 4 servings, add broccoli to a second sheet; roast chicken on top rack and broccoli on middle rack.)

Roast on top rack until broccoli is browned and tender and chicken is cooked through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> For a deeply golden crust, broil chicken for the last 2-3 minutes.

While chicken and broccoli roast, place potatoes in a large #pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes to pot.

Meanwhile, place @bacon{4%ounce} in a large, dry pan over medium-high heat. Cook, turning occasionally and adjusting heat if browning too quickly, until crispy, ~{6-10%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer bacon to a paper-towel-lined #plate{}. Once cool enough to handle, roughly chop.

To pot with drained potatoes, add @sour cream{2%tbsp}, remaining cheddar, and @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Mash until smooth and creamy with a #potato masher{}, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed.

Stir in half the bacon and half the chives. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide chicken, mashed potatoes, and broccoli between plates. Top mashed potatoes with remaining bacon and remaining chives. Serve.